## Summary
This documentation explains how to use predictive cohorts in marketing campaigns, including setting up campaigns across different channels (Facebook, Google, Braze, Iterable), measuring campaign results, and taking action based on those results. It covers three campaign types: inclusion criteria, dynamic pricing, and content personalization, with detailed instructions for synchronizing cohorts and analyzing performance differences between high and low probability user segments.

